The article discusses the shock and grief caused by another incident of gun violence in an American community on Independence Day. The author expresses gratitude for the first responders and law enforcement on the scene and offers the full support of the Federal government to the affected communities. Federal law enforcement has been deployed to assist in the search for the shooter, who is still at large. The author urges community members to follow guidance from local leadership and expresses concern for the victims. The author mentions signing bipartisan gun reform legislation into law but acknowledges that more work needs to be done to combat gun violence.